      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"help\" feels like such a hollow word right now. what am i supposed to do with help? talk about how much it hurts? how much i miss her? that doesn't change the fact that the person i was is dead. everything just feels so pointless. why is it considered \"right\" to just keep dragging this weight around for years? it honestly feels more like a punishment than living. sometimes i think the most peaceful thing would just be to not have to experience another second of this.",
